🌊 Maritime Weather Intelligence Dashboard

A real-time maritime weather monitoring system that provides safety insights for global ports using live meteorological data.
This project visualizes, analyzes, and assesses port safety conditions based on API data from OpenWeatherMap and StormGlass.

🚀 Features

🔄 Automated Weather Data Fetching

weather_updater.py retrieves temperature, wind speed, and weather conditions for all ports listed in final.csv.

Classifies port safety levels:

✅ Safe

⚠ Moderate

⚡ Dangerous

🚨 Worst

📊 Interactive Dashboard (Streamlit)

app.py provides:

Real-time port weather data by country

Interactive Folium map of port safety

Downloadable CSV reports

🌐 Web Interface (Flask)

maritime_weather_ui.py allows users to fetch and view weather conditions for custom coordinates using the StormGlass API.

🧠 Tech Stack
Component	Technology
Language	Python
Dashboard	Streamlit
Web Framework	Flask
Mapping	Folium
Data Processing	Pandas
APIs	OpenWeatherMap, StormGlass
⚙️ Setup Instructions
1️⃣ Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/maritime-weather-dashboard.git
cd maritime-weather-dashboard

2️⃣ Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt


Create a requirements.txt file containing:

streamlit
flask
pandas
requests
folium
streamlit-folium

3️⃣ Prepare Data

Ensure you have a CSV file named final.csv containing port data with these columns:

name, country, lat, lon

4️⃣ Run Weather Updater
python weather_updater.py


This script fetches live weather data and creates per-country CSV files in weather_by_country/.

5️⃣ Launch Dashboard (Streamlit)
streamlit run app.py

6️⃣ Optional: Run Flask UI
python maritime_weather_ui.py


Then open your browser at:
➡️ http://localhost:5000/

